The paper proposes an improvement to a technique for fast retrieval of similar time sequences, which suggests it falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and database (cs.DB) categories. The use of Fourier coefficients in the distance computation indicates it may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the experiments carried out on real and synthetic data suggest it may also fall under the signal processing (cs.SI) category.
